Liren Ding vs Ian Nepomniachtchi
Speed Chess Championship Chess.com
Sicilian, Najdorf, Opovcensky variation (B92)

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be2 e5 7. Nb3 Be7 8. Be3 Be6 9. O-O O-O 10. Qd3 Nbd7 11. Nd5 Bxd5 12. exd5 g6 13. a4 Ne8 14. a5 f5 15. f3 Bg5 16. c4 Rc8 17. Qd2 Bxe3+ 18. Qxe3 Nef6 19. Nd2 f4 20. Qf2 Qe7 21. b4 Kh8 22. Bd3 Qg7 23. Rac1 Qe7 24. Rfe1 Rc7 25. Nb3 Rfc8 26. Rc2 Kg7 27. Nd4 Nf8 28. Bf5 Ra8 29. Ne6+ Nxe6 30. Bxe6 Nd7 31. c5 dxc5 32. Bxd7 Rxd7 33. Rxc5 Rad8 34. d6 Rxd6 35. Rcxe5 Qf6 36. Re7+ Kh6 37. h3 Rd2 38. Qc5 Qb2 39. Rxh7+ Kxh7 40. Qe7+ Qg7 41. Qh4+ Kg8 42. Re7 Qh8 43. Qg5 R2d6 44. Kh2 Qf6

Follow games live here https://chess24.com/en/watch/live-tournaments/hamburg-fide-gp-2019

The second quarterfinal of the 2019 Chess.com Speed Chess Championship will be played today between Ian Nepomniachtchi and Ding Liren. The winner will play either Wesley So or Maxime Vachier-Lagrave next.

After Vladislav Artemiev eliminated Levon Aronian last week, we'll see two more quarterfinal matches this week in our Speed Chess championship, which has a total prize fund of $50,000.

Read more here https://www.chess.com/news/view/2019-speed-chess-championship-quarterfinals-preview
